<body>
<p></span><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:13pt"><b>Tasks</b></span></font><font color="#010101"></font></p>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">The Tasks Screen lists all the Tasks defined. It displays the Name, Status, Created Date, Due 
Date for each of the Task.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">If you wish to add, export, filter or search new Tasks, you can click on the <b>Red </b>Button at the right 
bottom corner of the screen.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">Select <b>+Add</b> Button if you wish to Add New Tasks. Please refer to the <b>Task Add</b> Section of the 
Help to get more details on that Screen.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">Select <b>Export </b>Button if you wish to transfer all the listed tasks to an external file system for further 
processing. Choose&#160; Excel(Microsoft Excel spreadsheet application) or to a file with the format 
CSV (Comma separated), XML(Extensible Markup language) or Text(flat text file).</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">Select <b>Search </b>Button if you wish to search the tasks based on <b>Created By </b>field. On selecting the 
Search button, you can provide the value for <b>Created By (Ex: </b>Name of the Person who created 
the task) and press the <b>Search </b>Button. This Action will list all the Tasks created by the Name of 
the Person provided in <b>Created By&#160;</b> criteria.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">Select <b>Filter </b>Button if you wish to view the tasks based on certain criteria like the 
Status(Pending/Completed),Task Created Date, Task Due Date, Tags(Associated Tags like 
Urgent etc) etc. You can either create a new filter or choose the already saved filter. The Default 
tab will be <b>+Create Filter</b></span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">To Create a new filter, provide the required details and choose the either of the below mentioned 
actions.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Apply Filter : </b>After selecting the values for Task Status, Task created Date, Task Due Date, tags 
etc. you can press the <b>Apply Filter </b>if you wish to make the <b>Filter Criteria </b>take effect immediately. </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Save Filter : </b>On the Other hand, if you wish to save the Filter for subsequent use, click on the 
<b>Save Filter </b>Button. The application will ask for the name for the Saved filter.Provide the same and 
click the <b>OK </b>Button. This Action will save the current filter in the <b>Saved Filter Tab.</b></span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">To Choose from a already Saved filter, click on the <b>Saved Filter Tab. </b>You can see all the Saved 
Filter names in the list. Choose the required Filter. Immediately you can see the Tasks that qualify 
the chosen filter being displayed in the list area at the bottom of the screen.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Edit : </b>Choose this function if you wish to change or modify the details of an existing Task. Please 
Refer the Section on Tasks Edit to get more details on its usage.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Copy : </b>Choose this function if you wish to create a new Task from an existing Task. Clicking on 
<b>Copy </b>Button will open the <b>Tasks Edit</b> Screen. You can change the name of the Task and re-use 
its contents as it is or with some changes. On confirming the contents, the system will create a 
new Task without disturbing the original task chosen for <b>Copy. </b>Please Refer the Section on Tasks 
Edit to get more details on its usage.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"><br />
</font></div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Complete: </b>Choose this function if you wish to update the <b>status</b> of any task as <b>Complete. 
</b>Clicking on the <b>Complete </b>Button will open a dialog box that asks for reconfirmation. Click on <b>OK</b> 
to confirm or <b>Cancel</b> to ignore the change. If you had chosen the <b>OK</b> button, you can see the 
Task Status of the current task changed to <b>Complete </b>from <b>Pending.</b></span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Assign: </b>Choose this function if you wish to assign the current Task to a specific staff(referred to 
as <b>Handler </b>in the application). On Clicking this button, a dialog box appears asking you to choose 
the <b>Handler</b> to whom you wish to allocate the task. You can assign the task to more than 1 
handler. After choosing the <b>Handler, </b>you can provide instructions or message and click on 
<b>Submit </b>to confirm or <b>Close </b>to ignore the assignment. Once you have assigned a <b>Task, </b>the 
person or application user to whom the task has been assigned will get a notification about the 
same.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Delete : </b>Choose this function if you wish to remove any of the Task from the list. You can only 
delete a Task whose status is <b>Completed.</b></span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
</body>
